{
  "texts": [
    "Under certain restrictions, the manufacture and trade of BSFL as feed is particularly permitted in the European Union, Australia, Canada, and the United States.",
    "It is interesting to note that while regulatory frameworks are now being developed, the majority of nations where entomophagy is a tradition lack particular restrictions regarding their usage as feed.",
    "Harmonizing the industrial upscaling of BSFL as animal feed requires an understanding of the legislative structure (Alagappan et al., 2022).",
    "It is necessary to enumerate the environmental effects connected with the entire life cycle of these processes in order to estimate the environmental profile of products derived from insects.",
    "An important method for analysing and assessing the environmental influence of industrial processes and insect-based products is life cycle assessment (LCA) (Spinelli et al., 2019)."
  ]
}